                                "start": 0,
                                "stop": 19.066,
                                "byte_start": 28672,
                                "byte_stop": 104950,
                                "text": "The judgment and opinion of the Court in No. 73-300, Saxbe against Bustos together with 73-480, Cardona against Saxbe will be announced by Mr. Justice Douglas."
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 19.066,
                        "stop": 144.077,
                        "byte_start": 104950,
                        "byte_stop": 605038,
                        "speaker": {
                            "ID": 15107,
                            "name": "William O. Douglas",
                            "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/people\/william_o_douglas",
                            "last_name": "Douglas",
                            "roles": [
                                {
                                    "id": 2751,
                                    "type": "scotus_justice",
                                    "date_start": -969127200,
                                    "date_end": 185004000,
                                    "appointing_president": "Franklin D. Roosevelt",
                                    "role_title": "Associate Justice of the Supreme Court of the United States",
                                    "institution_name": "Supreme Court of the United States",
                                    "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/preson_role\/scotus_justice\/2751"
                                }
                            ],
                            "thumbnail": {
                                "id": 32781,
                                "mime": "image\/png",
                                "size": 56651,
                                "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/sites\/default\/files\/william_o_douglas.png"
                            },
                            "length_of_service": 13358,
                            "identifier": "william_o_douglas"
                        },
                        "text_blocks": [
                            {
                                "start": 19.066,
                                "stop": 51.584,
                                "byte_start": 104950,
                                "byte_stop": 235039,
                                "text": "These cases are here on certiorari to the Court of Appeals for the District of Columbia and involve the construction of a rather obscure provision of the Immigration and Nationality Act, pertains to its application to people who come over from Mexico or from Canada each day to work and return at night."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 51.584,
                                "stop": 66.58,
                                "byte_start": 235039,
                                "byte_stop": 295016,
                                "text": "And also to those who would come over from Mexico or Canada to work for a season, like in a fruit harvest or wheat harvest, and return at the end of the season."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 66.58,
                                "stop": 81.468,
                                "byte_start": 295016,
                                "byte_stop": 354576,
                                "text": "Whether they are non-immigrants in which within the meaning of the Act in which event there have to be a certificate of the Secretary of Labor that they\u0027re not people available here to do that work."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 81.468,
                                "stop": 91.448,
                                "byte_start": 354576,
                                "byte_stop": 394491,
                                "text": "Or if they are immigrants, then they can -- having satisfied the other requirements of the Act can come without that certificate."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 91.448,
                                "stop": 102.736,
                                "byte_start": 394491,
                                "byte_stop": 439630,
                                "text": "There was a conflict between the Ninth Circuit that held that seasonal and daily commuters were covered by the immigration provision of the Act."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 102.736,
                                "stop": 117.513,
                                "byte_start": 439630,
                                "byte_stop": 498772,
                                "text": "And a ruling of the court below in this case had held if all daily commuters were covered, the seasonal commuters were not covered and therefore the seasonal workers would have to get a certificate from the Secretary of Labor."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 117.513,
                                "stop": 128.162,
                                "byte_start": 498772,
                                "byte_stop": 541403,
                                "text": "We agreed with the Court of Appeals to the Ninth Circuit and we think that all -- both daily and seasonal commuters are immigrants covered by that provision of the Act."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 128.162,
                                "stop": 144.077,
                                "byte_start": 541403,
                                "byte_stop": 605038,
                                "text": "Therefore we affirm in part and reverse in part the judgment of the Court of Appeals which Mr. Justice White has filed a dissenting opinion in which Mr. Justice Brennan, Mr. Justice Marshall, and Mr. Justice Blackmun have joined."
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    {
